com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.domain.web

Interface WebCmsSiteConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    WebCmsDomainUrlConfigurer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    WebCmsSiteConfigurationImpl

    public interface WebCmsSiteConfiguration
extends WebCmsDomainUrlConfigurer
    This is the default domain metadata interface for a WebCmsDomain representing a website. This is a common case where the WebCmsModule is used for multi-site management.
    Since:
    0.0.3
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration, WebCmsSiteConfigurationImpl

        <Y> Y getAttribute(String attributeName,

        Get the value of the attribute identified by attributeName. The value will be converted to the attributeType specified. Return null if the attribute doesn't exist.

        This variant uses the TypeDescriptor to define the attribute type, allowing for the use of parametrized types.
